TWENTY Beauties have qualified for Miss Tanzania Beauty Pageant to be staged on May 20th at Mlimani City Conference Hall in Dar es Salaam. Twenty ladies will compete in the pageant for a ticket to represent Tanzania in the Miss World finals. The Miss World contest will be staged on December 10th this year in Puerto Rico. On Thursday, Star Media announced its official partnership with Miss Tanzania contest 2022. The company stands as the event's primary sponsor and will manage the whole contest together with other partners. The national campaign begins today, when the ladies will camp ahead of the grand finale. Among the activities during the camp include swimming exercise, photographing, cooking, fashion and modelling. This was revealed during a press conference at Serena Hotel in Dar es Salaam. Star Media announced its plan to televise and create content throughout during the camp and broadcast on the Star Bongo channel. The National Arts Council (BASATA) Acting Executive Secretary Matiko Mniko congratulated the contestants and the committee involved. He noted he is excited to see the preparation of this year's Miss Tanzania contest is exhilarating and encouraged individuals, sponsors and the public to utilise this opportunity to support the government's efforts in promoting tourism in our country. As a special guest, Miss Tanzania 2020/2021 Rose Manfere urged the contestants to observe the rules in the camp and contest to avoid any inconveniences due to lack of discipline or proper behaviour. She added that the contestants will have a lot to learn during the contest. Many more opportunities will come along during these contests apart from just winning the prizes. The marketing manager of Star Times David Malisa announced the prize to be worth more than 20m/- together with a lot more bonuses that the contestants will be awarded from multiple activities that will be carried out during the camping period.